Social inequalities  

Nowadays social inequality is a major issue. Because of it the majority of people can not live as they wish. Social inequality occurs when resources in society distributed unevenly, it is a differentiation preference of social goods in a society brought about by power religion, gender, sexual orientation, prestige, physical characteristics. Norms of allocation can also affect distribution of rights and privileges, social power, access to public goods such as education, transportation, financial services. 

Equality is closely connected to the rights of people or human rights and I think, its necessary to defend and respect the rights of people regardless of their age, colour and other characteristics that were mentioned before. It is not a secret that our society structured into different classes. Class distinctions are often made on the basis of people’s incomes, social status. And as you go upper, you often have better access to quality education, better healthcare, good nutrition and other services. For instance, it is proof that 83% of students from high income families enroll in college after high school, only 63% of low income students do. Wealthier kids tend to live in higher income neighborhoods, which in turn fund better quality schools, this makes it easier to get into college. I think, inequality between rich and poor has a crucial impact on development. Because the irritating consumerism of the rich and the shortage of basic needs in low income societies lead to the multiplication of conflicts between the rich and poor which will cause criminal activities such as robbery and corruption. Gender inequality fills the violence that affects two out of three women from all over the world. Females often experience differences in terms of pay. For instance for the same position, they may be paid less than their male peers. So, in my opinion, it is the key reason why many women are dependent on men for financial support. I consider, gender inequality is a result of the belief that men and women have different rights and entitlements. Furtheremore, society categorizes people based on race, ethnicity and this ultimately creates a system that leads to inequality. Racial discrimination tends to have greater degrees of inequality, as manifested by lower salaries, lower educational opportunities, reduced access to healthcare. Racism includes beliefs, thoughts, and actions based on the idea that one race is innately superior to another race. It is found that black students with the same standartized test scores as their white classmates were less likely to be nominated for gifted programs if they had a non-black teacher. The professor may discriminate against you in turn by giving them a lower score than they deserve on their assessments. White and Asian students are more likely to chosen to be in honors than black and Hispanic students. This is an example of tracking, in which schools assign students to different types of educational programs.  

To conclude, social inequality is a serious problem and being an ethnic minority, racial minority, or being very poor puts you at a great social disadvantage in today`s world. However, if humans do not develop social mobility, countries can not develop too. Inequality threatens economic development and destroys people`s sense of self-worth. Everyone has a right to live without any discrimination.  Every individual has an equal opportunity to succeed in their life.
